nodes.text: The daughter of Imperial Admiral Winstel Greelanx was a female individual who was an adult and married by around 4 BBY. Greelanx loved his daughter. Consequently, when he feared retribution in the event that his deliberate defeat at the Battle of Nar Shaddaa be uncovered, he dismissed the idea of fleeing to save himself because that course of action would have likely resulted in his family's deaths.
